<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="115" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1059,1539,1656]" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">
COMMENTS: Within Neotropical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1829" box="[561,687,1539,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[561,687,1539,1562]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">Megarthrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuccodoro &amp; C. &amp; P. &amp; Ch-" authorityYear="2011" box="[702,810,1539,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="machu">
<emphasis box="[702,810,1539,1562]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">M. machu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished by its abruptly and broadly expanded elytra. Exceeding 
<quantity box="[792,861,1570,1593]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
in length (when measured from the middle of the frontal margin to the tip of the abdomen), it is the largest species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1839" box="[328,449,1633,1656]" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Proteininae">Proteininae</taxonomicName>
of the world. See comments under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bierig" authorityYear="2011" box="[833,965,1633,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adelphus">
<emphasis box="[833,965,1633,1656]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="115">M. adelphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
